<body>
  <TopBar />

  <Navigation />
  <main class="service-page service-page--compact">
    <section
      class="service-hero service-hero--trugreen service-hero--compact"
      style="background-image: url('/assets/Mulching_Service.jpg');"
    >
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-lg-9 col-xl-7 hero-content-block">
            <h1 class="mb-2">Mulching</h1>
            <h2 class="mb-3">Refresh your beds with a clean, finished look.</h2>
            <p class="mb-4 lead">
              Fresh mulch improves curb appeal while helping protect plants and soil.
              Our mulching service provides even coverage and clean bed edges for a professional finish.
            </p>
            <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Get a Free Quote</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="service-section service-section--compact">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="mb-3">What’s included with Mulching</h2>
        <div class="matrix-grid">
          <div class="matrix-card">
            <h3>Bed preparation</h3>
            <p>
              We clear out loose debris, tidy the beds, and create a clean base so new mulch
              looks crisp and performs better from the start.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="matrix-card">
            <h3>Even mulch installation</h3>
            <p>
              A consistent depth helps regulate soil temperature and moisture while giving your
              beds a rich, uniform appearance.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="matrix-card">
            <h3>Defined bed edging</h3>
            <p>
              Sharp, defined edges keep mulch where it belongs and make your beds stand out with
              clean, professional lines.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="matrix-card">
            <h3>Debris removal</h3>
            <p>
              We haul away loose debris and excess material so your landscape looks finished,
              tidy, and ready to enjoy.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="service-section service-section--compact">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="mb-3">Why Mulching Matters</h2>
        <ul class="bullet-list">
          <li>Enhances landscape appearance</li>
          <li>Retains moisture and protects roots</li>
          <li>Reduces weed growth</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="service-section service-section--compact">
      <div class="container">
        <div
          class="service-visual"
          style="--service-accent-start: #f8f2ea; --service-accent-end: #eedbc8; --service-accent-badge: #8b4f24;"
        >
          <div class="row align-items-center">
            <div class="col-lg-6 mb-4 mb-lg-0">
              <span class="service-visual__eyebrow">Fresh Finish</span>
              <h2 class="mb-3">Mulch that makes beds pop</h2>
              <p>
                A clean layer of mulch locks in moisture, keeps weeds down, and gives your beds a
                rich, finished look that highlights your plantings.
              </p>
              <ul class="pill-list">
                <li class="pill">Moisture shield</li>
                <li class="pill">Weed control</li>
                <li class="pill">Color refresh</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-6">
              <img
                class="service-visual__image"
                src="/assets/Mulching_Service.jpg"
                alt="Fresh mulch installed around landscape plants"
              />
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="service-section service-section--compact">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="mb-3">Benefits of Mulching in Lynchburg, VA</h2>
        <div class="matrix-grid">
          <div class="matrix-card">
            <h3>Moisture retention</h3>
            <p>Mulch helps soil stay hydrated longer, protecting roots during hot Central Virginia summers.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="matrix-card">
            <h3>Weed suppression</h3>
            <p>A clean mulch layer blocks sunlight to reduce weed growth and keep beds looking tidy.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="matrix-card">
            <h3>Enhanced curb appeal</h3>
            <p>Fresh mulch delivers a polished, finished look that highlights your landscape design.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="service-section service-section--compact">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="mb-3">How It Works</h2>
        <ol class="bullet-list">
          <li><strong>Assess:</strong> We review bed size, plantings, and your mulch preference.</li>
          <li><strong>Service:</strong> We prep the beds and install mulch evenly at proper depth.</li>
          <li><strong>Finish:</strong> We clean up and leave beds sharp and tidy.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="service-section service-section--compact">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="mb-3">Best Time to Schedule</h2>
        <p>Most customers refresh mulch in spring and/or fall.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="service-section service-section--compact">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <div class="service-accordion">
          <details open>
            <summary>How often should mulch be replaced?</summary>
            <p>
            Many properties benefit from refreshing mulch once per year. Sun exposure, slope, and rainfall can affect how quickly mulch breaks down.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>How much mulch do I need?</summary>
            <p>
            Mulch needs depend on bed size and the depth required. We typically aim for an even layer that looks clean and supports plant health.
            We’ll estimate volume during the quote.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Do you remove old mulch?</summary>
            <p>
            In most cases, we refresh by top-dressing. If mulch buildup is excessive or a bed needs reworking, we can discuss removal options.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Will mulch stop weeds completely?</summary>
            <p>
            Mulch helps reduce weeds, but it may not eliminate them entirely. Proper bed prep and ongoing maintenance usually provide the best results.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>What type of mulch is best?</summary>
            <p>
            Common choices include hardwood mulch and dyed mulch. The “best” option depends on your preference, budget, and the look you want for the property.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Can you mulch around trees?</summary>
            <p>
            Yes, but proper technique matters. We avoid piling mulch too high against trunks to help prevent moisture and rot issues.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Do you edge beds before mulching?</summary>
            <p>Yes. Clean bed edges create a sharp finish and help the mulch stay in place.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="service-section service-section--compact">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="mb-3">Related Mulching Articles</h2>
        <ul class="bullet-list">
          <li><a href="/blog/how-often-should-you-mulch-your-beds">How Often Should You Mulch Your Beds?</a></li>
          <li><a href="/blog/mulch-vs-rock-which-is-better">Mulch vs. Rock: Which Is Better?</a></li>
          <li><a href="/blog/best-mulch-depth-for-flower-beds">Best Mulch Depth for Flower Beds</a></li>
          <li><a href="/blog/how-to-prevent-weeds-in-landscape-beds">How to Prevent Weeds in Landscape Beds</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="service-section service-section--compact bg-light">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="callout-panel">
          <h2>Get a Free Quote</h2>
          <p>Tell us what beds you want mulched and your mulch preference, and we’ll provide pricing.</p>
          <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Request a Free Quote</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />

